entries.femaleVariant: There is one thing I will miss about Night City.
What's that?
The food. The Thai on Seventh in Heywood. The pierogis down by the docks. Mh…
You'll understand once you've ridden with us for a while.
I can smell the ozone, even through the air conditioning.
Seriously?
Panam! Girl, are you running from Night City or goin' to your granny's for cookies and milk? Gun it or that storm'll catch ya!
Screw you.
Mitch! Hey!
Hey, V.
Come on, Mitch, you weren't nearly that confident after Mikoshi, none of us were.
Did save every one of our asses, though.
Most of our people have already crossed. They'll wait for us on the other side.
And our souvenirs from Mikoshi?
If we so much as approached the gates with tech like that, they would wipe us out without warning. We've checked. Arasaka has people at every border crossing.
So, full circle – back to robbin' Arasaka…
Just hope this goes better than it did for me and Jackie.
Just realized – here I am, kleppin' from Arasaka again.
Arasaka... Deja vu.
Don't you worry. We'll pass right under the bastards' noses.
We better. New beginnings can be rough.
Don't you know it.
Did I say something wrong?
Just reminded me of Jackie. And the Arasaka job. Think you know how that ended.
I'm sorry, V.
C'mon. You had nothin' to do with that. Anyways, things'll be different now. Gotta be.
entries.maleVariant: C'mon. You had nothin' to do with that. And anyway, things'll be different now. Gotta be.

entries.femaleVariant: Can't wait.
Wonder if I'll miss the city, too.
Anything I could possibly miss I'm bringin' with me.
Really? Then I can't wait.
Wonder if I'll miss Night City, too.
Just realized – already bringin' everything I could possibly miss.
Of course, our new lives will be nothing but pure fucking chaos.
Of that, I have no doubt.
Doe'n't matter – gonna be a good life. I can feel it. And you'll sense it, too.
You will miss the Night City you imagined was there.
The city of endless potential, endless possibilities. The city that was a lie…
We'll handle it together. Even the memories of NC.
Fuck, V, you are a sweet-talker, aren't you.
But it works, doesn't it? Say it, say it works.
It works. All too well.
You're with me now. We will figure out and take care of that piece of shit in your head.
I know.
It's that storm. Gettin' close.
Good to hear you, choom! How's things?
Give me a month and I'll be as good as new. I told you all I'd be fine, didn't I?
A pity Saul's not with us. Or Teddy. Or Bobby. Or Scorpion…
I know, Panam, I know...
Gave us all a chance at a new start. Let's not fuck it up.
I'm glad you're with us, V. See you soon.
Gen'leman extraordinaire, Yorinobu Arasaka, confirmed that his sis, Hanako, was among the victims.
So it seems we've got a change acomin' at the tippity top of the megacorp. Soaked in the usual gallons of blood, sweat and tears, of course.
This is rot, I've heard enough.
They would've kicked your ass out of whack after that move with the panzer. Then hugged you until you puked.
He was in bed for weeks, a vegetable. It would've been the end of him if not for his synapses, toughened, made almost fry-proof in panzers back in the war.
But we know a road less traveled.
